From: qwen3-tts-native maintainers
Subject: [PATCH] build(arm64): drop unavailable torchcodec dependency

SGLang-Omni 0.1.0 declares torchcodec 0.11.1 unconditionally. That release has
no Linux ARM64 wheel. Qwen3-TTS uses PyAV on this platform, and the pinned
SGLang CUDA 13 runtime already provides the compatible media stack.

This is a packaging-only change. It does not modify Qwen3-TTS model execution,
scheduling, codec decoding, HTTP transport, or streaming behavior.
---
 pyproject.toml | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/pyproject.toml b/pyproject.toml
--- a/pyproject.toml
+++ b/pyproject.toml
@@ -65,7 +65,6 @@ dependencies = [
     "descript-audiotools",
     "descript-audio-codec",
     "torchaudio==2.11.0",
-    "torchcodec==0.11.1",     # Matches sglang==0.5.12.post1 dependency
     # Gradio playground
     "gradio>=4.0.0",
     # Ming-Omni
